race.comment: CANDO ATTITUDE (5) is a promising filly resuming for the Joseph & Jones team and remains unbeaten from two starts late last year. With natural improvement and a perfect draw, she should take plenty of stitching. VAINSTREAM (2), the evergreen 11-year-old, continues to race with enthusiasm and made light work of his rivals over this trip at Gundagai 13 days ago. Draws well again and deserves genuine respect. BRIDIE'S LUCK (3) hasn't struck this prep but is edging closer. She'll look the winner at some stage, though the big weight may test her late. ABSTRUSE (6) hasn't won for a long time but was a flashing light at Moruya last start. Worth keeping safe.
